{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content of each modified file.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Scoping failures usually happen at module boundaries (diff parser + prompt/input builder). A pure unit test of one function can miss wiring mistakes, malformed-hunk handling, or accidental fallback to full-file content.","test_description":"Run the review-input builder against realistic multi-hunk unified diffs (including context, additions, deletions, and renamed files) and assert the produced review payload contains only changed-line snippets plus required minimal context, never full-file bodies.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Correct diff-view positioning depends on GitHub’s real PR review-comment API semantics (commit SHA, side/line mapping, hunk context). In-process mocks commonly accept invalid mappings that real API rejects or reanchors differently.","test_description":"Against a real test PR, post inline comments for known target lines across multiple hunks/files, then fetch posted review comments from GitHub and verify each comment resolves to the expected file and diff position/line in the PR Files Changed view.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.8,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This checks model judgment quality on real code, which depends on non-deterministic LLM output. Deterministic mocks or rule stubs can pass while the real model misses the bug.","test_description":"Use a seeded PR containing a known bug (e.g., missing null check causing runtime failure), run the real reviewer model, and assert at least one inline finding correctly flags that defect class/location; evaluate over repeated runs with a pass-rate threshold to account for stochasticity.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary corresponds to an inline comment that was also posted — no findings appear in the summary without a matching inline comment.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The failure boundary includes real posting outcomes: inline post can fail (validation/rate limit/permission), while summary still gets posted. Mocked clients often hide this mismatch by always succeeding.","test_description":"Run on a real PR, then retrieve both the final top-level summary and all posted inline review comments via API. Parse finding identifiers (or normalized file+line+message keys) and assert summary findings are a subset of successfully posted inline findings.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.35,"System":0.5,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full sequence — reading the diff, posting inline comments, posting the summary comment — completes correctly for a real pull request without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is an end-to-end agent pipeline across multiple dependent steps, including at least one agentic analysis step plus external API actions. Single-step tests cannot expose cross-step state/ordering/idempotency failures.","test_description":"Execute the production automation against a real sandbox PR from trigger to completion, with no manual retries. Assert ordered completion of steps (diff ingested, inline comments created, summary posted), and verify final artifacts are internally consistent and linked to that run.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.35,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.45}}]}
